A certificate or evidence of a debt with a sum fixed as a penalty, which contains a written agreement binding the parties to pay the penalties. It contains a condition, however, that the payment of the penalty may be avoided by the performance by some one or more of the parties of certain acts. 

Source: [VA Circuit Court Civil Glossary](http://www.courts.state.va.us/courts/circuit/resources/manuals/cc_manual_civil/glossary.pdf)